======================================================================
LLM WALKTHROUGH TRANSCRIPT
======================================================================

OPENING:
----------------------------------------------------------------------
You find yourself in an overgrown garden, the air thick with the scent of damp earth and decaying leaves. Weeds have taken over the flowerbeds, choking out any remaining color. A weathered stone bench, its surface covered in soft moss, sits among the weeds. It looks sturdy enough to stand on. An old oak tree rises from the garden, its thick branches spreading wide overhead, offering a leafy canopy. High in the branches, a crystalline star glows with a warm inner light. A weathered stone path leads north, winding through the overgrown garden toward the tower entrance. The path looks inviting, though the garden itself feels a bit daunting.

======================================================================
TURN 1: stand on bench
----------------------------------------------------------------------

PROSE:
You stand on the bench, feeling its cool, moss-covered surface beneath your feet. The bench is weathered stone, sturdy and well-made, but the moss that clings to it gives it a slightly eerie, natural feel. From your elevated position, you can see the garden in a new light, the plants and paths below appearing more detailed and vibrant.

======================================================================
TURN 2: examine mat
----------------------------------------------------------------------

PROSE:
You look around the room from your elevated position on the bench, but you don't see any mat here. The floor is made of rough stone, and the only exit is a stone path leading north to the Tower Entrance.

======================================================================
TURN 3: climb tree
----------------------------------------------------------------------

PROSE:
You climb the ancient oak, your hands gripping the thick gnarled branches as you make your way up the tree. The leafy canopy above provides a cool and quiet respite from the sun, and you can feel the rough bark against your palms as you climb higher and higher.

======================================================================
TURN 4: take star
----------------------------------------------------------------------

PROSE:
You climb higher into the tree, the branches creaking beneath your weight. The star, a warm radiance in your palm, catches the light as you hold it close. Its crystalline facets sparkle, each one reflecting the sun's rays back at you. It's a beautiful, familiar yet magical object that you can't help but marvel at.

======================================================================
TURN 5: down
----------------------------------------------------------------------

PROSE:
You carefully climb down from the tree, your feet finding purchase on the rough bark as you make your way to the ground. The grass beneath you is soft and cool, a stark contrast to the warmth of the sun on your skin while up in the branches. You take a moment to catch your breath and survey your surroundings, ready to continue your exploration.

======================================================================
TURN 6: north
----------------------------------------------------------------------

PROSE:
You step onto the north stone path and make your way to the Tower Entrance. The entrance hall of the tall stone tower greets you, dust motes dancing in the shafts of light that filter through the narrow windows. The air is filled with a musty, earthy scent, and the room feels both welcoming and a bit foreboding.

You notice a faded welcome mat with barely visible words "Speak Friend" woven into the fabric. It's worn from years of foot traffic, and a layer of dust covers its surface. To one side, there's a simple umbrella stand, holding an old, slightly weathered umbrella. The wooden door to the east stands slightly ajar, and to the south, a garden archway leads to the Overgrown Garden.

Exits lead east (wooden door), up (spiral staircase to Wizard's Library), and south (garden archway to Overgrown Garden).

